                    "measure": "Patient-reported outcome",
                    "description": "Patient Reported Outcomes of Fracture Healing",
                    "timeFrame": "up to 24 months"
                }
            ]
        },
        "eligibilityModule": {
            "eligibilityCriteria": "Inclusion Criteria:\n\n* Radiologically confirmed open physis in the injured bone at time of injury\n* Diagnosis of an isolated fracture according to the AO PCCF\n* Willingness and ability of the patient/parents/legally responsible care giver to participate in the registry, including obtaining imaging and adhering to follow-up procedures according to standard of care in each clinic\n* Willingness and ability of the parent(s) to support the patient in his/her study participation\n* Ability of parents or a legal guardian to understand the content of the patient information/ICF and to sign and date the IRB/EC approved written informed consent form\n\nExclusion Criteria:\n\n* Radiologically confirmed closed physis in the injured bone at time of injury\n* Polytrauma/multiple fractures\n* Previous fracture of the same anatomical region\n* Underlying musculoskeletal or neuromuscular disorder\n* Present to participating centers with a displaced humeral fracture, tibial shaft fracture, forearm fracture, or femoral neck fracture at greater than 4 weeks postinjury\n* Unable to provide the legal consent\n* Inability of the patient/parents/legally responsible caregiver to participate in imaging and/or FU procedures",
            "sex": "ALL",
            "maximumAge": "18 Years",
            "stdAges": [
                "CHILD",
                "ADULT"
            ],
            "studyPopulation": "Consecutive pediatric patients with key long bone fractures.",
            "samplingMethod": "PROBABILITY_SAMPLE"
        },
